title: Google\Cloud\Compute\V1\TargetVpnGateway
name: TargetVpnGateway
description:
Represents a Target VPN Gateway resource. The target VPN gateway resource represents a Classic Cloud VPN gateway. For more information, read the the Cloud VPN Overview.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.compute.v1.TargetVpnGateway

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data.name
params.description: Name of the resource. Provided by the client when the resource is created. The name must be 1-63 characters long, and comply with RFC1035. Specifically, the name must be 1-63 characters long and match the regular expression [a-z]([-a-z0-9]*[a-z0-9])? which means the first character must be a lowercase letter, and all following characters must be a dash, lowercase letter, or digit, except the last character, which cannot be a dash.

params.name: data.network
params.description: URL of the network to which this VPN gateway is attached. Provided by the client when the VPN gateway is created.

params.name: data.region
params.description: [Output Only] URL of the region where the target VPN gateway resides. You must specify this field as part of the HTTP request URL. It is not settable as a field in the request body.

params.name: data.self_link
params.description: [Output Only] Server-defined URL for the resource.

params.name: data.status
params.description: [Output Only] The status of the VPN gateway, which can be one of the following: CREATING, READY, FAILED, or DELETING. Check the Status enum for the list of possible values.

params.name: data.tunnels
params.description: [Output Only] A list of URLs to VpnTunnel resources. VpnTunnels are created using the compute.vpntunnels.insert method and associated with a VPN gateway.
